The paper proposes a method for clustering using bootstrapping and finite mixture models, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also deals with uncertainty and probability, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
